//////////// firebase with nodejs

firebase is a google product which is used to store data in cloud,
It is a NoSQL database.(JSON format),
npm init ,
press enter sevaral times,
npm install express body-parser firebase-admin,
npm i nodemon ,then auto refresh server,
npm i dotenv,
create index.js file,
create firebase project in website,
project settings -> service accounts -> copy code,
add it to index.js 
const admin = require("firebase-admin");

const serviceAccount = require("path/to/serviceAccountKey.json");

admin.initializeApp({
  credential: admin.credential.cert(serviceAccount)
});
genarate privatekey and put it in to project and set it path in code,
create a database in firebase,
built -> firestore database -> create database -> start in test mode,
add database url in code,
const db = admin.firestore();
const app = express();
app.use(bodyParser.json());
const collection = 'customers';
then implement the code,

to run project type in cmd "nodemon" and press enter,

///////////////// mysql with nodejs

npm uninstall mysql,
npm install mysql2,
create a database in mysql,

CREATE DATABASE test1;
USE test1;
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS customer(
    id VARCHAR(45) PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(45) NOT NULL DEFAULT "unknown",
    address VARCHAR(45) NOT NULL,
    salary DECIMAL(10, 2)
);
SHOW TABLES;
DESC customer;

